cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on deep learning architecture and its application in mobile cloud computing services. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses image processing and computer vision techniques, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as another likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a training method for compensating for accuracy loss, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of cloud computing and mobile devices suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses energy consumption, which is related to optimization techniques and falls under the scope of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
